bluez:
------
sudo apt-get install bluez-hcidump
sudo apt-get install libglib2.0-dev
sudo apt-get install libapparmor1
sudo apt-get install libdbus-1-dev
sudo apt-get install libudev-dev
sudo apt-get install libreadline-dev
sudo apt-get install libical-dev
sudo apt-get install gawk


sudo apt-get install bluez-hcidump libglib2.0-dev libapparmor1 libdbus-1-dev libudev-dev libreadline-dev libical-dev gawk

sudo systemctl enable bluetooth.service
sudo usermod -G bluetooth -a pi

sudo ./sixpair
power off and power on...



joystick:
--------
sudo apt-get install joystick



mqtt:
------
sudo apt install -y mosquitto mosquitto-clients
sudo systemctl enable mosquitto.service

sudo pip3 install paho-mqtt



.profile:
---------
add to the bottom

PATH=$PATH:/home/pi/pyros/bin


/boot/config.txt:
-----------------

disable w1 interface


network interfaces:
-------------------

sudo pip3 install netifaces


networking on type-c - natting usb0:
------------------------------------

# sudo iptables -F
# sudo iptables -t nat -F
# sudo iptables -t nat -A POSTROUTING -o wlan0 -j MASQUERADE
# sudo iptables -A FORWARD -i wlan0 -o usb0 -m state --state RELATED,ESTABLISHED -j ACCEPT
# sudo iptables -A FORWARD -i usb0 -o wlan0 -j ACCEPT

Manual setup that worked:

sudo iptables -A FORWARD -i usb0 -o wlan0 -j ACCEPT
sudo iptables -A FORWARD -i wlan0 -o usb0 -j ACCEPT
sudo iptables -t nat -A POSTROUTING -o wlan0 -j MASQUERADE


uncomment net.ipv4.ip_forward=1 in /etc/sysctl.conf

Copy these two files:

--- /lib/dhcpcd/dhcpcd-hooks/80-usb0
# usb0 up after assign ip address
# echo >> /home/pi/80-usb.log "$interface $reason"
if [ "$interface" = "usb0" ] && [ "$reason" = "STATIC" ]; then
        # echo >> /home/pi/80-usb.log " matched: "
        # ifconfig usb0 169.254.1.1/16
        # echo >> /home/pi/80-usb.log " set address "
        iptables-restore < /etc/iproute2/usb0_rules
        # echo >> /home/pi/80-usb.log " set iptables "
fi
---

